{
  "texts": [
    "Pre-trained models based on transformers, such as BERT (Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers) and the GPT (Generative Pre-trained Transformer) series, have revolutionized NLP.",
    "These models enable researchers to fine-tune contextual embeddings for specific applications, offering a significant leap forward in the ability to vectorize and analyze text at both the word and document levels.",
    "Importantly, many of these approaches can be further fine-tuned via supervised learning to improve performance based on the type of corpus.",
    "For example, Bekamiri, Hain and Jurowetzki (2024) and Ghosh, Erhardt, Rose, Buunk and Harhoff (2024) respectively developed PatentSBERTa and PaECTER, two embedding models that build on BERT but are specifically trained on patent documents to capture semantic relationships across patents.",
    "Compared to off-the-shelf embeddings trained on general English text, these specialized models could in principle improve the precision of any NLP task that is applied on comparable corpora."
  ]
}